      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/22/5211",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ أُمَّهُ قَالَ \"لاَ يَرِثُهَا وَ يُقْتَلُ بِهَا صَاغِراً وَ لاَ أَظُنُّ قَتْلَهُ بِهَا كَفَّارَةً لِذَنْبِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5211 - Ibn Mahbub narrated from Ali ibn Ri'ab from Abu Ubaydah, who said:\nI asked Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a man who killed his mother.\nImam (as) said: \"He does not inherit from her, and he is to be executed for her murder in a state of humiliation.\nYet, I do not believe that his execution will serve as an expiation for his sin.\""
        ]
      }
    },
